definition: Terminology relevant to the category of cell phenotyping tests.
name: Category for Cell Phenotyping
preferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Category for Cell Phenotyping Terminology

terms.definition: An assay type that examines a cellular pathway or biological process.
An assay type that examines the types of markers or antigens associated with the cell surface, nucleus, or cytoplasm.
An assay type that examines the interaction of ligands with their target biomolecules.
